BT /F1 9 Tf 72 718 Td (Version: 4.2 | Effective Date: 2025-01-01 | Owner: VP, Tax Controversy) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 72 700 Td (================================================================================) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 72 678 Td (1. Purpose and Scope) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 656 Td (This manual establishes the policies and procedures for responding to tax audits and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 642 Td (examinations by federal, state, and international tax authorities. It applies to all) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 628 Td (personnel in the American Express Enterprise Tax Department and external advisors engaged) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 614 Td (in audit defense.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 588 Td (The manual covers: initial audit notification processing, document retention and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 574 Td (production, IDR response protocols, taxpayer position development, appeals and settlement) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 560 Td (procedures, and post-audit remediation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 72 538 Td (2. IDR Response Protocol) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 516 Td (Upon receipt of an IDR: \(1\) Log the IDR in the Tax Controversy Management System within 24) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 502 Td (hours. \(2\) Assign a lead analyst based on the subject matter. \(3\) Schedule a kickoff) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 488 Td (meeting with the lead analyst, tax controversy manager, and relevant subject matter) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 474 Td (experts within 3 business days. \(4\) Prepare a response timeline -- default 30 days from) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 460 Td (receipt. \(5\) Draft responses undergo two levels of review: technical review by a tax) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 446 Td (director and legal privilege review by Corporate Legal. \(6\) Final responses are approved) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 432 Td (by the VP, Tax Controversy before submission.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 72 410 Td (3. Document Production Guidelines) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 388 Td (All documents produced to tax authorities must be reviewed for: \(a\) attorney-client) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 374 Td (privilege -- work product or communications with legal counsel must be withheld or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 360 Td (redacted; \(b\) relevance -- only documents responsive to the specific IDR request should be) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 346 Td (produced; \(c\) confidentiality -- PII including Social Security numbers, individual) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 332 Td (compensation amounts, and customer data must be redacted unless specifically requested and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 318 Td (legally required; \(d\) consistency -- ensure documents are consistent with prior productions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 304 Td (and publicly filed returns.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 72 282 Td (4. Escalation Procedures) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 260 Td (Escalation to the SVP, Tax and/or General Counsel is required when: \(a\) proposed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 246 Td (adjustments exceed $50M for a single issue, \(b\) the examiner requests documents that may) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 232 Td (be subject to attorney-client privilege, \(c\) the examining agent threatens summons) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 218 Td (enforcement, \(d\) the audit involves coordination with DOJ Tax Division or criminal) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 204 Td (investigation, \(e\) settlement negotiations involve concessions that would establish) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 82 190 Td (unfavorable precedent for future tax years.) Tj ET
